{{Quote|Long have I waited, for my grandchild to come home! I never wanted you dead. I wanted you here, Empress Palpatine.|Darth Sidious, to Rey|<ref name="TROS">{{Film|IX}}</ref>}}
[[File:DarkReyLightsaber-TLC.png|thumb|right|280px|Rey had visions in which she was corrupted by the dark side and took the Sith throne.]]
'''Empress''' was a title of a ruler. [[Millennium|Millennia]] before the [[Republic Era|fall]] of the [[Galactic Republic]], the [[Color|blue]]-skinned [[Anselmi]] formed their own [[Anselmi empire|empire]] on [[Glee Anselm]], ruled by an [[Unidentified Anselmi empress|empress]].<ref name="Vengeful Waves">{{StoryCite|story=Vengeful Waves|book=Myths & Fables}}</ref> When [[Galactic Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]] ruled the [[Galactic Empire]], Empress [[Leeya]] governed the [[Regency Worlds]].<ref name="Dawn">''[[Dawn of Rebellion]]''</ref> Later, Palpatine revealed that he was the [[Dark Lord of the Sith|Sith Lord]] [[Darth]] Sidious and urged his [[Palpatine family|granddaughter]], the [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] [[Rey Skywalker|Rey]], to give into the [[Dark side of the Force|dark side]] by [[Death|killing]] him and claim the [[Throne of the Sith]] as Empress. The [[Sith Lord]] embodied those who came before him and sought to [[Transference|transfer]] his spirit into Rey's body and conquer Rey, but she affirmed that she was a Jedi and ultimately [[Battle of Exegol|defeated]] Sidious.<ref name="TROS" />

